CAPE TOWN - Cape Town City Manager Achmat Ebrahim has resigned with immediate effect. Ebrahim who is fingered in an alleged multimillion-rand tender fraud in the Foreshore Freeway Precinct tender, resigned from his position as of Friday, 12 January 2018. In his resignation letter, he says he is able to quite easiy defend the allegations made against him and would furnish the Mayor's office with copies of all the evidence files. Ebrahim has denied the allegations against him as baseless. Cape Townâ€™s City Manager resigns. #DeLille https://t.co/aHi8z9P0Qo eNCA